marble /ˈmɑːbəl/

(marbles) 

1. N-UNCOUNT Marble is a type of very hard rock which feels cold when you touch it and which shines when it is cut and polished. Statues and parts of buildings are sometimes made of marble. 大理石 

例： The house has a superb staircase made from oak and marble. 这座房子里有用栎木和大理石做成的一流的楼梯。 

2. N-COUNT Marbles are sculptures made of marble. 大理石雕像 

例： ...marbles and bronzes from the Golden Age of Athens. …雅典全盛时期的大理石雕像和青铜像。 

3. N-UNCOUNT Marbles is a children's game played with small balls, usually made of coloured glass. You roll a ball along the ground and try to hit an opponent's ball with it. 弹子游戏 

例： On the far side of the street, two boys were playing marbles. 在这条街的那一头，两个男孩子正在玩弹子游戏。 

4. N-COUNT A marble is one of the small balls used in the game of marbles. 弹子 

例： ...a glass marble. …一个玻璃弹子。

